The paper deals with inapproximability results for LPs and SDPs, which are topics related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The reduction mechanism used in the paper is a minor restriction of classical reductions used in PCP theorems, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions results for CSPs, which are related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
